            <title>[HBASE-11692] Document how and why to do a manual region split</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11692</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;---------- Forwarded message ----------&lt;br/&gt;
From: Liu, Ming (HPIT-GADSC) &amp;lt;ming.liu2@hp.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date: Tue, Aug 5, 2014 at 11:28 PM&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: Why hbase need manual split?&lt;br/&gt;
To: &quot;user@hbase.apache.org&quot; &amp;lt;user@hbase.apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Hi, all,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As I understand, HBase will automatically split a region when the region is too big.&lt;br/&gt;
So in what scenario, user needs to do a manual split? Could someone kindly give me some examples that user need to do the region split explicitly via HBase Shell or Java API?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks very much.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Ming&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
